div.div: Akuyaku Reijou Level 99: Watashi wa Ura Boss desu ga Maou de wa Arimasen

This college kid wants nothing more than a quiet life. So when she’s reborn as Yumiella, the hidden villainess of an Otome RPG, she’s not exactly thrilled. Still yearning for peace, she abandons her evil duties to live a more discreet life. Until her gamer side kicks in and she accidentally reaches level 99! Now, everyone suspects that she’s the infamous Demon Lord. What future awaits her?
(Source: Crunchyroll)
Goukon ni Ittara Onna ga Inakatta Hanashi

College student Tokiwa gets invited to a mixer by his female classmate Suo. But when he arrives with his friends, they're greeted by three dazzlingly handsome men?! But as the two groups get to know each other, they find themselves getting closer in unexpected ways. (Source: MANGA UP!) Note: Each episode streamed 1 week early on ABEMA. The original TV broadcast started on October 4th 2024.

The story follows a unambitious introverted middle school student called Saike Kuzushiro. After witnessing the death of his childhood friend, Mikan Karatachi, in a road accident. He cries out to God and after a fall, Saike wakes up in bed the previous morning, the day of the accident. Will history repeat? Can he save Mikan? What power does he have to change the future? Included one-shots: Volume 3: The Negatibrain

Leticia Dorman is living every girl’s dream—she’s the daughter of a duke who’s grown up in the lap of luxury and she’s engaged to none other than the handsome crown prince, Clarke. But this dream is her nightmare! In preparation to become part of the royal family, Lettie has endured ten painful years of lessons on everything from dancing to etiquette. Her only chance of escape lies in the prince breaking off their engagement, which seems unlikely…until he shows up at a royal ball with a mysterious woman. This could be her chance to break free, but not if Prince Clarke has anything to say about it!
(Source: Seven Seas Entertainment)
